===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A public [[official]] whose duty it is to [[administer]] the [[law]], especially by [[presiding]] over [[trial]]s and [[render]]ing [[judgment]]s; a [[justice]].
# A [[person]] who [[decide]]s the [[fate]] of someone or something that has been [[call]]ed into [[question]].
# A person [[officiate|officiating]] at a [[sports]] or similar [[event]].
#: ''At a boxing match the decision of the '''judges''' is final.''
# A person whose [[opinion]] on a [[subject]] is [[respect]]ed.
#: ''He is a good '''judge''' of wine.''

